On Fox Across America with Jimmy Failla, Rep. Doug Collins (R-GA) discussed the light he has been portrayed in while running for US Senate from both of the other candidates in the race.

"They tried to make me out to be a liberal. They tried to make me out to be a moderate. It's just been amazing. But that's what you're having one of the biggest political, most expensive political makeovers in history and didn't have a fundamental backing of what you believe when you ran. It's been pretty hilarious down here and if the crowds have had any question about if I'm a conservative or not, just go Pelosi, Schiff, and Nadler, they'll tell you who the conservative is."
